@node eplay "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "MiniKonnex" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on a game board that varies from a 5 by 5
tiles board up to 9 by 9 tiles board... in other words, the size
you have choosen. To play, click on a small square tile, the links
surrounding it will rotate clockwise by 90 degrees.

  The goal is to connect together all the links of the tiles on the
game board, in the least amount of moves. When the game board is
completed, MiniKonnex will generate a new game board...

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:

  'New Game' button:   To restart the game.

  '+' and '-' buttons: To change the game board's size. If you
                       click on the '+' button while the game board
                       is at its maximum size, it will display a
                       board in the 5 by 5 tiles size... the
                       opposite will happen if you click on the '-'
                       button and the game board is at its minimum
                       (5 by 5) size...

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

